type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|v0.1.79 |2026-06-15 |''Fix: cascade-palette rows whose caption / title / value contains a doublequote no longer silently vanish (JSON escaping in hand-built rows).'' cascade-palette parses every `ca-items-from` row with JS `JSON.parse` and silently drops (console.warn) any row whose JSON is invalid. The kind plugin builds many rows by string-concatenation into `"…"` JSON literals; an unescaped `"` (or `\`) in an embedded value broke the JSON and dropped that row. ''Reported via'' //Referenced by… → "Conversation (as Participants)"//: conversations whose `caption` contained a `"` were missing from the list. ''Fix:'' new `kind.json-escape(value)` helper (escapes `\` then `"`); `kind.kv` now routes its value through it — fixing `kind.instance-row-json` (the reported case) and every kv-based builder. Every inline row builder that embeds user-controlled ''display'' text now escapes it at its capture point: instance/ref/clone display names, kind captions, computed `Save as "…"` / collision / save-warning titles, relation labels (//(as …)//), multi-value text entries, enum-option toggles (`ca-true-value` still round-trips to the raw value via JSON.parse), and — in `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` — manage-kinds / clone-kind / child-kind / field-hint / auto-child / wizard step-name / blocked-step rows. Filter operands (`ca-next-scope`, `ca-items-from`), type-key slugs, and the already-escaped delete-`consequence` text are deliberately left raw. Verified by CLI-rendering the real chains with `"`-bearing captions/options/step-names — all rows now parse and round-trip. (Residual, separate: a `"` inside a tiddler ''title'' inlined into a `ca-actions` attribute makes the row parse/show but the action could misfire when fired — needs a variable-based fix; `ca-icon` left unescaped as a negligible admin-set field.) ''Touches:'' `cascade-helpers.tid`, `palette/cascade-helpers.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Macro tiddlers — re-read on render (browser reload), no server restart. |
|v0.1.78 |2026-06-11 |''Notes side-preview: note-kind restriction + empty-note init.'' Two follow-ups to the v0.1.77 ''Notes'' preview. ''(1) Note-kind restriction'' — the related-notes list is now restricted to instances whose `kind.type` is one of the configured note-kinds (new config tiddler `$:/config/rimir/kind/notes-preview/kinds`, space-separated, default `note`), applied at `kind.note-referrers` so it covers BOTH the `parent`-children path and the back-ref-referrer path. So a non-note child — e.g. a conversation that merely has the instance as `parent` — is no longer listed; only actual notes are. The instance's OWN content is always shown first regardless of its kind. Widen by editing the config (e.g. `note p-note`). New helpers `kind.note-kinds` / `kind.note-kind-ok`. ''(2) Empty-note init'' — an empty note (no `text` and no `stream-list`) now offers two ways to start its content without leaving the pane: the ''stream'' path is Streams' OWN ''＋'' add-node button — `kind.note-stream-slot` now renders the `nodes-list-template` for empty notes too, and the native ''＋'' creates the first node and drops straight into edit mode (correctly `<<qualify>>`'d, since it is the native template); the ''text'' path is a new ''✎ Text'' button that sets `$:/state/rimir/kind/notes/text-edit` to that note, flipping its body to an inline `$edit-text` textarea on the `text` field (''✓ Done'' clears the state). Keystrokes reach the textarea, not the palette input, via cascade-palette's activeElement guard. New helpers `kind.note-empty` / `kind.note-stream-slot` / `kind.note-text-editing`; new `.kind-notes-init` / `.kind-notes-textedit` / `.kind-notes-textarea` styles. ''Touches:'' `palette/preview/notes.tid`, `config-notes-preview-kinds.tid` (new), `styles.tid`, `readme.tid`, `doc/overview.tid`, `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Template/config tiddlers — server restart re-bundles the changed plugin files (incl. the new config tiddler). |
|v0.1.77 |2026-06-11 |''New ''Notes'' side-preview — own content + every note that points here.'' A cascade-palette side-preview (`palette/preview/notes`, tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/side-preview`, `ca-preview-applies: [<currentTiddler>has[kind.type]]`) that, for the selected kind-instance, renders its OWN content first — its `text` body (block-transcluded) and, if it is a Streams root, its note-structure — then every kind-instance that points to it: typed children (`parent` field) unioned with back-ref referrers (every back-navigable ref field, via `kind.qual-source-kinds` / `kind.qual-back-fields` / `kind.referencing-instances`), de-duplicated and sorted `created` descending. Stream child-nodes are excluded from the list by the `has[kind.type]` gate (they render inside their root's stream block, not as standalone notes). A ''View'' pill toggles two layouts, each backed by a `$:/state/rimir/kind/notes/*` tiddler so the toggle refreshes the pane in place: ''Stream'' (default — notes stacked, newest at top) and ''Tabbed'' (one pill per note, the instance itself leftmost then referrers newest-first, active note's body shown below; the active pill self-heals to the instance when the stored choice isn't in the set). Streams render via `$:/plugins/sq/streams/nodes-list-template` with double-click in-place editing intact (needs cascade-palette ≥ 0.0.129 for editor focus/keystrokes in the pane). Streams is a SOFT dependency — the stream block only renders when it's installed AND the note has a `stream-list`. ''Touches:'' `palette/preview/notes.tid` (new), `styles.tid`, `readme.tid`, `doc/overview.tid`, `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Template/config tiddlers — picked up after a server restart (new plugin-bundled tiddler). |
|v0.1.76 |2026-06-11 |''Creation wizard: date-step pre-fill + force-land-in-optional.'' Two new wizard-step props, for richer date steps (driver: a 4-step tickler wizard). ''(1) `ca-step-date-default`'' — on a ''date'' field step, a smart-date / offset expr (e.g. `+2w`) injected as `ca-date-default` on the field row, so when the single-field step auto-opens its editor the palette seeds the still-blank date (pre-fill). In edit mode the value can be nudged with `+/-` (Shift ±month, Ctrl ±year), typed, or picked from a calendar popup (when cascade-palette's `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/date-picker-module` is configured). Wiring: `kind.wiz-assemble-field` threads the field JSON through `kind.wiz-inject-date-default` → `kind.wiz-date-default-append` (reads `ca-step-date-default`; harmless on non-date rows). ''(2) `ca-step-auto-edit: yes`'' — forces a single-field step to auto-open its editor even when the field is already ''valid'' (normally only invalid steps auto-open; a valid step auto-advances). For an OPTIONAL field the user should still land in — e.g. tickler's `until`: land in the empty date editor, ↵-on-empty to continue (single-date reminder) or set a date (duration). Wiring: `kind.wiz-auto-mode-gate` now ORs invalid-ness with the flag via new `kind.wiz-auto-edit-flag`. ''(3) Finish returns to the entity'' — the wizard's terminal ''✓ Create'' / auto-''Creating…'' rows now carry `ca-after-fire: pop-to-actions` (like the parent-pick step), so a wizard whose last step is a plain field (e.g. tickler: caption → when → until, with the Subject pre-seeded to the launching instance) creates and pops back to that entity's action menu instead of closing the palette. Needs cascade-palette ≥ 0.0.127. ''Touches:'' `palette/cascade-helpers.tid`, `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Macro tiddler — re-read on render (browser reload), no server restart. |
|v0.1.75 |2026-06-10 |''Creation wizard: preferred spawn-locations per instance.'' An instance can carry a `kind.spawn-locations` field (a title-list); when you run ''Create here…'' from that instance and reach a `ca-step-pick-tree` parent-picker step, those locations are surfaced as ★-marked rows pinned to the ''top'' of the picker — above the ⇄ Switch row, in ''both'' the tree and flat layouts, and regardless of which kind is being created (one list per instance). Picking a ★ row behaves exactly like any other node (commit + finalise + per-node context-graph preview + `pop-to-actions` return), giving one-keystroke placement into a frequent parent. ''Reading'' (`palette/cascade-helpers.tid`): the `host-tid` — previously dropped at `kind.wizard-field-rows` — is threaded down the picker chain to `kind.wiz-pick-roots-call`, whose `ca-items-from` assembly grows from `[switch] [nodes]` to `[preferred] [switch] [nodes]` (`kind.wiz-pick-roots-call-2/-3` + `kind.wiz-join-three`); new producer `kind.wiz-preferred-roots` → `kind.wiz-pref-row` → `kind.wiz-pref-json` reads `host get[kind.spawn-locations]enlist-input[]` and reuses the tree leaf's pick action (`kind.wiz-tree-pick-action`) + row-extras (`kind.wiz-row-extras` = graph preview + `pop-to-actions`), just with a ★ icon. A location is NOT de-duplicated against its natural tree/list position — the ★ copy is the shortcut; empty/missing field → no ★ rows. ''Defining'': new addable common field `common-fields/spawn-locations.tid` (def key `kind.spawn-locations`, typed `ref`/`multi`, ★) — add via //+ Add field from library…// and edit per-instance in //Edit fields//; the picker reads the field directly, so setting `kind.spawn-locations` on any instance works even without adding it to the schema. ''Touches:'' `palette/cascade-helpers.tid`, `common-fields/spawn-locations.tid` (new), `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Macro/config tiddlers — re-read on render (browser reload), no server restart needed (no JS change). |
|v0.1.74 |2026-06-10 |''Creation wizard: runtime tree⇄flat switch for the parent-picker.'' A `ca-step-pick-tree` step now opens a ''switchable'' picker with a pinned ''⇄ Switch'' row at the top: flip between the drillable namespace ''tree'' and a ''flat'' candidate list (the field's `kind.ref-candidates`) without leaving the flow. The layout is ''remembered per step'' in a persisted JSON-map config tiddler `$:/config/rimir/kind/wizard/pick-mode` (keyed by step title); `ca-step-pick-tree` accepts `yes`/`tree` (default tree) or `flat` (default flat). Both layouts keep pick = create, the per-node context-graph preview, and `pop-to-actions` return. ''Mechanism'' (no cascade-palette/JS change): the field row's `ca-items-from` is built as `[switch-row] [tree-or-flat-roots]` per the saved mode, and its `ca-auto-token` becomes `<wizidx>-<gen>` (a monotonic per-step switch counter in `$:/state/rimir/kind/wizard/pick-gen`) so every flip re-arms the auto-open into the other layout — without the counter, tree→flat→tree would reuse a fired token and stall on the 3rd switch; the ⇄ leaf (`ca-after-fire: pop`) `jsonset`s the new mode + bumps the counter and bounces to the wizard stage. ''Wiring:'' `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` — `kind.wiz-pickable` / `kind.wiz-pick-mode(-default/-saved)` gate + mode, `kind.wiz-pick-roots-call` / `-nodes-call` / `-switch-call` / `-flat-roots-call` item-set builders, `kind.wiz-switch-*` row, `kind.wiz-flat-roots` / `-flat-row` (reuse `kind.ref-candidates` + `kind.wiz-tree-leaf-row`), `kind.wiz-pick-token`, `\procedure kind.wiz-toggle-pick-mode`. ''Touches:'' `palette/cascade-helpers.tid`, `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Macro/config tiddlers — re-read on render, but a server restart re-bundles the changed plugin file. |
|v0.1.73 |2026-06-10 |''Creation wizard: hands-free landing + drillable tree parent-picker.'' Polishes the v0.1.72 wizard into a near-zero-clutter flow. ''(1) Direct landing'' — a single-field step now auto-opens its one input: a text/enum step lands straight in value-edit mode (↵ commits → advances), a ref step straight in the picker (via cascade-palette `ca-auto`/`ca-auto-token`). A non-selectable heading bar above the input names each step (`ca-stage-heading` on the swapping wizard stage, `ca-next-heading` on a pushed picker). So a guided create is mostly ''type · ↵ · pick · ↵''. ''(2) Tree parent-picker'' (`ca-step-pick-tree: yes` on a single-ref step) — instead of the flat ref list, the field renders a drillable namespace hierarchy (same structure as //By Namespace//): Right-arrow descends into a node's children, ↵ on //any// node commits it as the value AND finalises the instance (pick = create, via `ca-enter-fires`). Structure comes from `ca-step-pick-roots` (default config `$:/config/rimir/kind/wizard/pick-roots`) + `…/pick-children` (the `cp-child-of` namespace tree). ''(3) Per-node graph preview'' — each focused tree node shows its kind context graph in the side preview (the shared `palette/preview/context` template, per-row). ''(4) Return-to-entity'' — after the create the palette stays open and pops back to the action menu of the entity you launched ''Create here…'' from (cascade-palette `ca-after-fire: pop-to-actions`) instead of closing. ''Fix:'' child-node detection used a bare `subfilter{…}` which doesn't rebind `<currentTiddler>`; wrapped in `:map:flat` so the namespace filter resolves each node's children. ''Wiring:'' new tree engine in `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` (`kind.wiz-tree-*`, `kind.wiz-row-extras`, `kind.wiz-node-ctx-kv`, `kind.wiz-child-nodes`/`-root-nodes`/`-has-children`); `cascade-helpers.tid` wizard fresh-start; two new config tiddlers (`config-wizard-pick-roots.tid`, `config-wizard-pick-children.tid`). Requires cascade-palette ≥ 0.0.126. ''Touches:'' `palette/cascade-helpers.tid`, `cascade-helpers.tid`, `config-wizard-pick-roots.tid` (new), `config-wizard-pick-children.tid` (new), `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Macro/config tiddlers — re-read on render, but a server restart re-bundles the changed plugin files. |
|v0.1.72 |2026-06-10 |''Designer-defined creation wizards.'' A kind can now be created through an ordered, guided, multi-step flow in the cascade-palette instead of a single all-fields form — so a TW-inexperienced user is asked only the currently-relevant field(s) per step and never has to open //Edit fields//. ''Authoring:'' each step is a tiddler tagged `$:/tags/rimir/kind/wizard-step` with `ca-wizard-kind` (target type-key), `ca-wizard-context` (host type-key this variant applies to; empty = default), `ca-order`, `ca-step-name`, `ca-step-fields` (space-separated field keys) and optional `ca-step-hint`. Steps are resolved per (target, host) with context-specific overriding default. ''Flow:'' the whole wizard occupies one drill stage backed by a per-draft step-index state tiddler; a progress row (//Step n of m//), the step's field editor rows (reusing `kind.field-edit-json`, so every field type incl. the ref picker works), and ''← Back'' / ''Next →'' / ''✓ Create'' nav leaves. ''Next'' is gated per step by `kind.viol-any` (blocks with a ⛔ row until the step's required/format constraints pass); the final ''Create'' re-checks `kind.any-invalid` then runs `kind.finalize-create`. The parent/back-ref is pre-seeded from the launch context but a `parent` step lets the user redirect it — solving the "everything created from a person is forced under that person" pain. ''Wiring:'' `kind.cascade-create-here-fields` now routes through `kind.cchf-route` → emits the wizard when one exists for (target, host), else the original flat form; `kind.cascade-create-here-init` restarts the wizard at step 1 on each drill-open. New engine in `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` (`kind.wizard-*`, `kind.cchf-*`, `kind.wizard-finish`); `cascade-helpers.tid` gains the 1-line route + idx-reset. ''Touches:'' `cascade-helpers.tid`, `palette/cascade-helpers.tid`, `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Shadow/Macro tiddlers — re-read on render, but a server restart is needed to re-bundle the changed plugin files. Step tiddlers themselves are plain wiki tiddlers (live, no restart). |
|v0.1.71 |2026-06-09 |''Fix: auto-children now reliably inherit their parent.'' `kind.finalize-create` created the parent instance with `$action-createtiddler` and then ran `kind.apply-auto-children` as a //sibling//, reading the new title back via `parent-tid={{{[<savetitle>get[text]]}}}`. But `$action-createtiddler` exposes the real post-uniquification title only to its ''children'' (the `<<createTiddler-title>>` variable + a `refreshChildren()` call, both fired before the child action chain runs); the change event that would update a sibling is async, so the sibling read happened at render time and saw a stale/empty `savetitle`. Result: the auto-child's `parent` came out empty (e.g. a conversation's "Minutes" note got title `_notes/minutes` instead of `<conversation>/_notes/minutes`), intermittently depending on what the last save left in `savetitle`. Fix: nest the `apply-auto-children` transclude ''inside'' the `$action-createtiddler` and pass `parent-tid=<<createTiddler-title>>` — the actual created title, re-evaluated before the auto-child actions fire. Benefits all save paths (creator, cascade save / spawn / create-here, graph-modal). ''Touches:'' `engine.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Shadow tiddler (a `\procedure`) — a server restart is needed to re-bundle it into the plugin. |
|v0.1.70 |2026-06-09 |''Reverse-reference navigation — the "Referenced by…" drill'' (`engine.tid` + `cascade-helpers.tid` + new `actions/referenced-by.tid`). From any kind instance (a ref endpoint, e.g. a person), drill back to the instances that reference it (e.g. the conversations it participates in). ''Discovery'' (`engine.tid`): `kind.referencing-instances(host, source-type, field)` is the core — instances of a kind whose ref field points at the host; `kind.qual-source-kinds` / `kind.qual-back-fields` / `kind.back-rel-count` enumerate which source kinds reference the host through a `back-nav`-enabled field that has ≥1 instance. ''Listing'' (`cascade-helpers.tid`): `kind.referenced-by-items` builds the drill rows — exactly one incoming relation collapses straight to the instance list; ≥2 surface an entry-level row per relation (//Conversation (as Participants)//, label overridable via a `back-label` field prop). Instance rows carry the real `title` (so Space opens the entity's Open / Edit / Delete via the action bridge) and a `ca-group` cluster. ''Per-kind config'' read off the SOURCE type def: `kind.back-group-by` (cluster field, e.g. `status`), `kind.back-sort-by` (sort field, descending / newest-first, default `modified`); per-`ref`-field `back-nav: no` opts a relation out. These same primitives back `rimir/worga`'s conversation drills. ''Touches:'' `engine.tid`, `cascade-helpers.tid`, `actions/referenced-by.tid` (new), `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Shadow / Macro tiddlers + a new action tiddler — re-read on render, but a server restart is needed to bundle the new files into the plugin. |
|v0.1.69 |2026-06-09 |''Fix: Instances Overview edge selection now persists across reload.'' The edge-selector stored its titlelist in a field literally named `fields`, which collides with the TiddlyWeb sync wire-format's reserved `fields` container (`tiddlywebadaptor.js` puts every non-standard field into a hashmap named `fields`) — so the value was silently dropped on every browser→server save and the graph always reverted to the `parent` default. Renamed the field to `edges` in both the //Instances Overview// config tiddler and the //Context// preview state tiddler (`config-instances-overview-edge-fields.tid`, `instances-overview.tid`, `palette/preview/context.tid`); the read also floors to `parent` when unset (`~[[parent]]`), so the default edge is always drawn and the `parent` checkbox shows ticked by default. Edges keep the native checkbox UI. Shadow/template tiddlers — re-read on render, but a server restart is needed to pick up the renamed shadow default. |
|v0.1.68 |2026-06-08 |''Quick-create, per-ref "Manage…" actions, and a duration widget'' (all in `cascade-helpers.tid` + one new provider tiddler; needs cascade-palette ≥0.0.123). ''(1) Quick-create (`kind.qc-*`).'' A reduced create drill that shows only a declared subset of fields, prefills the rest, and derives the `caption` from a per-action formula — the formula lives on a `<draft>/qcmeta` sidecar (so its brackets never become a filter operand) and is recomputed via an injected `ca-on-commit` on each edited field, so a dated caption flows into a unique slug title through the existing title-formula. Safety net: any required-but-unsatisfied field still surfaces as an edit row, and the reused Save row ⛔-blocks until valid. ''(2) Per-ref "Manage…" actions.'' New `palette/manage-refs-provider.tid` (tagged `…/cascade-palette/action-provider`) + `kind.manage-ref-actions`: surfaces one ''"Manage <field>…"'' action per reference field on any kind instance, drilling straight into the existing ref picker (multi → add/remove toggles, single → pop-select). ''(3) Duration widget'' (consumes cascade-palette's new `daterange` kind). `kind.qc-range-fields` emits a `daterange` row for a paired start/end (e.g. `when`/`until`) with per-action default offsets + the caption-refresh on-commit; `kind.edit-range-items` binds a `daterange` directly to an ''existing'' record for in-place duration editing (seed-when-empty leaves current values intact). Shadow/Macro tiddlers — re-read on render, no restart needed. |Cascade-palette ref / enum field pickers now show the ''currently-selected entries on top, the rest alphanumerically by displayed name'' (`cascade-helpers.tid`). The picker drill (`kind.collection-build`, used by every ref / enum field — single & multi) gains `ca-sort-rows: name`, opting its rows into cascade-palette's data-row sort: multi-select toggles that are currently on float to the top (the palette reads the toggle's bind state), then the rest sort by their resolved display name (caption). For single-select `leaf` pickers (ref + enum), which carry no bind state, the row matching the current field value is marked `ca-selected: yes` (new `kind.collection-is-current` helper + `kind.ref-leaf-build2` / `kind.enum-leaf-build`) so the palette can float it too. Needs cascade-palette ≥0.0.122. ''Touches:'' `cascade-helpers.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Shadow tiddler only (Macro definitions) — re-read on render, no restart needed. |
|v0.1.66 |2026-06-04 |Kind icon lens now declares `ca-lens-actions: via-entity-type` — it owns the kind ''Open / Edit / Delete'' actions through cascade-palette's new lens-action bridge, so those actions stay available on every kind row even when the ''Icon'' lens slot is turned off (the actions are always-on, gated only by `ca-lens-when`, never by slot selection). Behaviour-preserving for users; declarative for the new contract. Needs cascade-palette ≥0.0.111. |
|v0.1.65 |2026-06-04 |Cascade-palette "Kind icons" migrated from the removed structure-toggle to a ''Kind'' icon ''lens'' (`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/lens`, slot `icon`, gated by `ca-lens-when` on kind types existing). Selectable in the palette's ''Icon'' slot strip; same behaviour (each kind instance shows its `kind.icon`, off by default, persists across reloads). Needs cascade-palette ≥0.0.110. |
|v0.1.64 |2026-06-04 |Graph tooltip node actions + modal: hover tooltip on every kind-graph node (Instances Overview + Context preview) gains ''edit'' (live field editor in a modal), ''delete'' (confirm dialog; disabled with a hint while the node has `parent`-field children — guard re-checked in the modal) and ''Add child'' buttons for every kind whose `parent` ref field accepts the node's type (plus `kind.parent-kinds` children, `kg.child-kinds`). Create reuses the standard editor + `kind.finalize-create` with parent pre-filled and defaults applied. New `$:/plugins/rimir/kind/graph-modal` overlay (`$:/tags/AboveStory`, layered above the cascade-palette); tooltip buttons dismiss the graph popup on click. |
|v0.1.63 |2026-06-03 |Cascade-palette "Kind icons" structure toggle — when on, every menu row backed by a kind instance shows its type's `kind.icon` glyph at the front (all views, persists across reloads). Off by default; appears only while a kind type exists. Needs cascade-palette ≥0.0.109. |
